    "GPT-4 has been shown to outperform GPT-3.5 on a variety of benchmarks, particularly in zero-shot reasoning tasks (Espejel et al., 2023).",
    "We therefore compare the performance of GPT-3.5 and GPT-4 on two datasets, a dataset of US political fact-checked claims provided by PolitiFact (Misra, 2022) and a dataset of multilingual fact-checked claims provided by Data Common.",
    "As GPT-3.5 is openly available to the public for free, it is used substantially more used than",
